<subSubSection lastPageId="21" lastPageNumber="22" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="20.[189,342,1909,1935]" box="[189,342,1909,1935]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,342,1909,1935]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,342,1909,1935]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Distribution</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[189,1399,1956,2018]" lastBlockId="21.[189,1399,267,400]" lastPageId="21" lastPageNumber="22" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
Recent records of this species are from the southern rim of the 
<collectingRegion box="[897,995,1956,1982]" country="Albania" name="Shkoder" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Shkodër</collectingRegion>
Lake Basin, from the surroundings of 
<collectingRegion box="[223,323,1991,2017]" country="Albania" name="Shkoder" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Shkodër</collectingRegion>
. The 
<collectingRegion box="[390,488,1991,2017]" country="Albania" name="Shkoder" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Shkodër</collectingRegion>
site is located on Upper Triassic, the Drisht site on Middle Triassic and the Renc Mts site on Upper Cretaceous limestone. If these were the only known localities, this would already make 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gittenberger" authorityYear="1969" box="[358,472,303,329]" class="Gastropoda" family="Spelaeodiscidae" genus="Virpazaria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="ripkeni">
<emphasis box="[358,472,303,329]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">V. ripkeni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the widest distributed species of its genus. Strangely, the 
<typeStatus box="[1171,1222,303,329]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">type</typeStatus>
locality of the nominate subspecies is located at the northwestern side of the 
<collectingRegion box="[921,1019,338,364]" country="Albania" name="Shkoder" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Shkodër</collectingRegion>
Lake Basin, very far from these Albanian sites (but see Remarks).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="22" lastPageNumber="23" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="21.[189,303,446,472]" box="[189,303,446,472]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,303,446,472]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,303,446,472]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[189,1399,492,941]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
This species was described on the basis of eight specimens. Their width and height are 3.5–4.0 mm and 
<quantity box="[242,420,527,554]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.15" metricValueMax="2.25" metricValueMin="2.05" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" unit="mm" value="2.15" valueMax="2.25" valueMin="2.05">2.05–2.25 mm</quantity>
, respectively, and the number of ribs on the last whorl is 73–86. In the original description (
<bibRefCitation author="Gittenberger E." box="[339,560,563,590]" firstAuthor="Gittenberger" journalOrPublisher="Zoologische Mededelingen" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="287 - 306" part="43" refId="ref12709" refString="Gittenberger E. 1969. Beitrage zur Kenntnis der Pupillacea. I. Die Spelaeodiscinae. Zoologische Mededelingen 43 (22): 287 - 306." title="Beitrage zur Kenntnis der Pupillacea. I. Die Spelaeodiscinae" type="journal article" year="1969">Gittenberger 1969</bibRefCitation>
) somewhat lower values were given, probably because he applied a different measuring method. The 
<typeStatus box="[582,685,598,624]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[725,891,599,624]" class="Gastropoda" family="Spelaeodiscidae" genus="Virpazaria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="pastorpueri">
<emphasis box="[725,891,599,624]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">V. pastorpueri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is 
<quantity box="[925,1016,598,625]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.6" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" unit="mm" value="3.6">3.6 mm</quantity>
wide and 
<quantity box="[1137,1242,598,625]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.15" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" unit="mm" value="2.15">2.15 mm</quantity>
high with 60 ribs on its last whorl (although 
<bibRefCitation author="Reischutz A. &amp; Reischutz N. &amp; Reischutz P. L." box="[558,825,633,660]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Reischutz" journalOrPublisher="Nachrichtenblatt der Ersten Vorarlberger Malakologischen Gesellschaft" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="57 - 60" part="18" refId="ref13283" refString="Reischutz A., Reischutz N. &amp; Reischutz P. L. 2011. Anmerkungen zur Verbreitung von Virpazaria Gittenberger 1969 (Spelaeodiscidae: Gastropoda) und bemerkenswerte Mollusken aus Albanien. Nachrichtenblatt der Ersten Vorarlberger Malakologischen Gesellschaft 18: 57 - 60." title="Anmerkungen zur Verbreitung von Virpazaria Gittenberger 1969 (Spelaeodiscidae: Gastropoda) und bemerkenswerte Mollusken aus Albanien" type="journal article" year="2011">
Reischütz 
<emphasis box="[681,733,633,659]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">et al</emphasis>
. (2011)
</bibRefCitation>
provided a smaller width (3.0– 
<quantity box="[1195,1289,633,660]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" unit="mm" value="3.5">3.5 mm</quantity>
), a larger height (
<quantity box="[281,377,668,695]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" unit="mm" value="2.5">2.5 mm</quantity>
) and an average of 65 ribs on the last whorl). Smaller and more tapered shells were defined by 
<bibRefCitation author="Reischutz A. &amp; Reischutz N. &amp; Reischutz P. L." box="[326,601,704,730]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Reischutz" journalOrPublisher="Nachrichtenblatt der Ersten Vorarlberger Malakologischen Gesellschaft" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="57 - 60" part="18" refId="ref13283" refString="Reischutz A., Reischutz N. &amp; Reischutz P. L. 2011. Anmerkungen zur Verbreitung von Virpazaria Gittenberger 1969 (Spelaeodiscidae: Gastropoda) und bemerkenswerte Mollusken aus Albanien. Nachrichtenblatt der Ersten Vorarlberger Malakologischen Gesellschaft 18: 57 - 60." title="Anmerkungen zur Verbreitung von Virpazaria Gittenberger 1969 (Spelaeodiscidae: Gastropoda) und bemerkenswerte Mollusken aus Albanien" type="journal article" year="2011">
Reischütz 
<emphasis box="[452,514,704,730]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">et al.</emphasis>
(2011)
</bibRefCitation>
as the most important features to distinguish 
<taxonomicName box="[1162,1331,705,730]" class="Gastropoda" family="Spelaeodiscidae" genus="Virpazaria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="pastorpueri">
<emphasis box="[1162,1331,705,730]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">V. pastorpueri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gittenberger" authorityYear="1969" box="[189,304,739,765]" class="Gastropoda" family="Spelaeodiscidae" genus="Virpazaria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="ripkeni">
<emphasis box="[189,304,739,765]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">V. ripkeni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Later, 
<bibRefCitation author="Gittenberger E." box="[400,636,739,766]" firstAuthor="Gittenberger" journalOrPublisher="Basteria" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="23 - 29" part="79" refId="ref12813" refString="Gittenberger E. 2015. Caving for snails in northern Albania. Basteria 79 (1 - 3): 23 - 29." title="Caving for snails in northern Albania" type="journal article" year="2015">Gittenberger (2015)</bibRefCitation>
studied a larger series of topotypical 
<taxonomicName box="[1097,1266,740,765]" class="Gastropoda" family="Spelaeodiscidae" genus="Virpazaria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="pastorpueri">
<emphasis box="[1097,1266,740,765]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">V. pastorpueri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
specimens and concluded that their shells are neither smaller nor relatively higher and thicker discoid than those of typical 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gittenberger" authorityYear="1969" box="[275,386,809,835]" class="Gastropoda" family="Spelaeodiscidae" genus="Virpazaria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="ripkeni">
<emphasis box="[275,386,809,835]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">V. ripkeni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, he found that the ribbing of 
<taxonomicName box="[844,1009,810,835]" class="Gastropoda" family="Spelaeodiscidae" genus="Virpazaria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="pastorpueri">
<emphasis box="[844,1009,810,835]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">V. pastorpueri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is less dense (less than 70 ribs on the last whorl) and therefore he preserved it as a distinct subspecies, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="- Gittenberger" authorityYear="2015" box="[993,1249,844,870]" class="Gastropoda" family="Spelaeodiscidae" genus="Virpazaria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Mollusca" rank="subSpecies" species="ripkeni" subSpecies="pastorpueri">
<emphasis box="[993,1249,844,870]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">V. ripkeni pastorpueri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In the same paper, Gittenberger described another subspecies, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gittenberger" authorityYear="2015" box="[787,987,880,906]" class="Gastropoda" family="Spelaeodiscidae" genus="Virpazaria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Mollusca" rank="subSpecies" species="ripkeni" subSpecies="arbeni">
<emphasis box="[787,987,880,906]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">V. ripkeni arbeni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which is smaller (H 
<quantity box="[1248,1394,880,906]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.75" metricValueMax="1.8" metricValueMin="1.7" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" unit="mm" value="1.75" valueMax="1.8" valueMin="1.7">1.7–1.8 mm</quantity>
; W 3.0– 
<quantity box="[277,367,915,941]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.1" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" unit="mm" value="3.1">3.1 mm</quantity>
) and has a weakly developed peristome.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[189,1399,988,1402]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
We collected several hundred specimens of this species at four different locations in the Renc Mts. Their shell width ranges between 2.7 and 
<quantity box="[603,695,1023,1050]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.6" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" unit="mm" value="3.6">3.6 mm</quantity>
, shell height between 1.5 and 
<quantity box="[1042,1131,1023,1050]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.1" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" unit="mm" value="2.1">2.1 mm</quantity>
and the number of ribs on the last whorl between 60 and 82. Compared to topotypical 
<taxonomicName box="[936,1102,1059,1084]" class="Gastropoda" family="Spelaeodiscidae" genus="Virpazaria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="pastorpueri">
<emphasis box="[936,1102,1059,1084]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">V. pastorpueri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, their size, shape and rib density values largely overlap. Although one might say that they are generally somewhat smaller and more tapered than typical 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gittenberger" authorityYear="1969" box="[503,617,1129,1155]" class="Gastropoda" family="Spelaeodiscidae" genus="Virpazaria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="ripkeni">
<emphasis box="[503,617,1129,1155]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">V. ripkeni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, neither these characters nor the rib density are able to provide a clear-cut distinction. This large variability in rib density refutes Gittenberger’s argument (
<bibRefCitation author="Gittenberger E." firstAuthor="Gittenberger" journalOrPublisher="Basteria" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="23 - 29" part="79" refId="ref12813" refString="Gittenberger E. 2015. Caving for snails in northern Albania. Basteria 79 (1 - 3): 23 - 29." title="Caving for snails in northern Albania" type="journal article" year="2015">Gittenberger 2015</bibRefCitation>
), and makes any distinction between 
<taxonomicName box="[689,854,1200,1225]" class="Gastropoda" family="Spelaeodiscidae" genus="Virpazaria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="pastorpueri">
<emphasis box="[689,854,1200,1225]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">V. pastorpueri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gittenberger" authorityYear="1969" box="[911,1022,1199,1225]" class="Gastropoda" family="Spelaeodiscidae" genus="Virpazaria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="ripkeni">
<emphasis box="[911,1022,1199,1225]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">V. ripkeni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
meaningless. However, none of the many adult specimens from the Renc Mts have such a weakly developed peristome as in the three specimens that were described as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gittenberger" authorityYear="2015" box="[596,796,1269,1295]" class="Gastropoda" family="Spelaeodiscidae" genus="Virpazaria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Mollusca" rank="subSpecies" species="ripkeni" subSpecies="arbeni">
<emphasis box="[596,796,1269,1295]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">V. ripkeni arbeni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Having no more material available from the 
<typeStatus box="[1348,1399,1270,1296]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">type</typeStatus>
locality of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gittenberger" authorityYear="2015" box="[322,456,1305,1331]" class="Gastropoda" family="Spelaeodiscidae" genus="Virpazaria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Mollusca" rank="subSpecies" species="ripkeni" subSpecies="arbeni">
<emphasis box="[322,456,1305,1331]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">V. r. arbeni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingRegion box="[474,578,1305,1332]" country="Albania" name="Shkoder" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Shkodër</collectingRegion>
), it is not possible to test whether the entire population consistently has an underdeveloped peristome there or the subspecies was described on the basis of three freak individuals. Until this question is settled, we must preserve 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gittenberger" authorityYear="2015" box="[889,1085,1375,1401]" class="Gastropoda" family="Spelaeodiscidae" genus="Virpazaria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Mollusca" rank="subSpecies" species="ripkeni" subSpecies="arbeni">
<emphasis box="[889,1085,1375,1401]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">V. ripkeni arbeni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[189,1399,1448,2003]" lastBlockId="22.[189,1399,267,435]" lastPageId="22" lastPageNumber="23" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
The type material of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gittenberger" authorityYear="1969" box="[458,576,1448,1474]" class="Gastropoda" family="Spelaeodiscidae" genus="Virpazaria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="ripkeni">
<emphasis box="[458,576,1448,1474]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">V. ripkeni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was presumably collected by Petar Dabović in the 1930s, passed somehow to the Viennese private collector Aemilian Edlauer, and finally landed in the NHMW Mollusc Collection. It appears that Edlauer, or someone else who studied his collection, recognized, but never described, three different species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gittenberger" authorityYear="1969" box="[646,771,1555,1580]" class="Gastropoda" family="Spelaeodiscidae" genus="Virpazaria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[646,771,1555,1580]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Virpazaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The proposed names were ʻ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fehér &amp; Deli &amp; Erőss &amp; Lika" authorityYear="2019" box="[1141,1382,1554,1580]" class="Gastropoda" family="Trissexodontidae" genus="Trissexodon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="kusceri">
<emphasis box="[1141,1382,1554,1580]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Trissexodon kuščeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
ʼ, ʻ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fehér &amp; Deli &amp; Erőss &amp; Lika" authorityYear="2019" box="[199,512,1589,1615]" class="Gastropoda" family="Trissexodontidae" genus="Trissexodon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="montenegrina">
<emphasis box="[199,512,1589,1615]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Trissexodon montenegrina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
ʼand ʻ 
<taxonomicName authority="Kaufeli" authorityName="Kaufeli" box="[583,819,1589,1615]" class="Gastropoda" family="Trissexodontidae" genus="Trissexodon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[583,819,1589,1615]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Trissexodon Käufeli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
ʼ. The latter name was obviously proposed for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gittenberger" authorityYear="1969" class="Gastropoda" family="Spelaeodiscidae" genus="Virpazaria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="pageti">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">V. pageti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but the situation is more dubious with the other two. Among the lots of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gittenberger" authorityYear="1969" box="[1144,1281,1624,1650]" class="Gastropoda" family="Spelaeodiscidae" genus="Virpazaria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="adrianae">
<emphasis box="[1144,1281,1624,1650]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">V. adrianae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
we could find both ʻ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fehér &amp; Deli &amp; Erőss &amp; Lika" authorityYear="2019" box="[311,545,1659,1685]" class="Gastropoda" family="Trissexodontidae" genus="Trissexodon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="kusceri">
<emphasis box="[311,545,1659,1685]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Trissexodon kuščeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
ʼ and ʻ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fehér &amp; Deli &amp; Erőss &amp; Lika" authorityYear="2019" box="[621,932,1659,1685]" class="Gastropoda" family="Trissexodontidae" genus="Trissexodon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="montenegrina">
<emphasis box="[621,932,1659,1685]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Trissexodon montenegrina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’ labels, whereas the name ʻ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fehér &amp; Deli &amp; Erőss &amp; Lika" authorityYear="2019" class="Gastropoda" family="Trissexodontidae" genus="Trissexodon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="kusceri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Trissexodon kuščeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’ also appears in the material of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gittenberger" authorityYear="1969" box="[651,764,1694,1720]" class="Gastropoda" family="Spelaeodiscidae" genus="Virpazaria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="ripkeni">
<emphasis box="[651,764,1694,1720]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">V. ripkeni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Gittenberger E." box="[779,1012,1694,1721]" firstAuthor="Gittenberger" journalOrPublisher="Zoologische Mededelingen" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="287 - 306" part="43" refId="ref12709" refString="Gittenberger E. 1969. Beitrage zur Kenntnis der Pupillacea. I. Die Spelaeodiscinae. Zoologische Mededelingen 43 (22): 287 - 306." title="Beitrage zur Kenntnis der Pupillacea. I. Die Spelaeodiscinae" type="journal article" year="1969">Gittenberger (1969)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned eight type specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gittenberger" authorityYear="1969" box="[222,334,1730,1756]" class="Gastropoda" family="Spelaeodiscidae" genus="Virpazaria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="ripkeni">
<emphasis box="[222,334,1730,1756]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">V. ripkeni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the same original lot (of which one was designated as a 
<typeStatus box="[1073,1179,1730,1756]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">holotype</typeStatus>
, one made its way to the RMNH and six remained in the original vial and kept the original labels (NHMW 77153a)). Interestingly, another site, “Pečina Grbočica bei Virpazar”, is indicated on the original label in that vial, whereas “Soko Höhle bei Dupilo”, which is given in the description, can be found on a newer label written in someone else’s handwriting. Furthermore, there is another lot (NHMW 77154), which is from Soko Cave according to the original label and contains one specimen of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gittenberger" authorityYear="1969" box="[1026,1137,1906,1932]" class="Gastropoda" family="Spelaeodiscidae" genus="Virpazaria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="ripkeni">
<emphasis box="[1026,1137,1906,1932]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">V. ripkeni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but not mentioned by 
<bibRefCitation author="Gittenberger E." box="[189,425,1941,1968]" firstAuthor="Gittenberger" journalOrPublisher="Zoologische Mededelingen" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="287 - 306" part="43" refId="ref12709" refString="Gittenberger E. 1969. Beitrage zur Kenntnis der Pupillacea. I. Die Spelaeodiscinae. Zoologische Mededelingen 43 (22): 287 - 306." title="Beitrage zur Kenntnis der Pupillacea. I. Die Spelaeodiscinae" type="journal article" year="1969">Gittenberger (1969)</bibRefCitation>
. Even stranger, this lot contains an original Edlauer label with the same locality, the same voucher number (E-57441) and the same proposed name, ʻ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fehér &amp; Deli &amp; Erőss &amp; Lika" authorityYear="2019" box="[945,1179,1976,2002]" class="Gastropoda" family="Trissexodontidae" genus="Trissexodon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="kusceri">
<emphasis box="[945,1179,1976,2002]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Trissexodon kusceri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’, as the type lot of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gittenberger" authorityYear="1969" box="[189,325,267,293]" class="Gastropoda" family="Spelaeodiscidae" genus="Virpazaria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="adrianae">
<emphasis box="[189,325,267,293]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">V. adrianae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It seems very difficult, if not impossible, to trace back whether there was any mixup with the labels or the specimens in the past, and, if so, where exactly the type specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gittenberger" authorityYear="1969" box="[1216,1328,303,329]" class="Gastropoda" family="Spelaeodiscidae" genus="Virpazaria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="ripkeni">
<emphasis box="[1216,1328,303,329]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">V. ripkeni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
came from (Soko?, Grbočica? or from somewhere else?). The fact that neither 
<bibRefCitation author="Gittenberger E." box="[1030,1263,338,365]" firstAuthor="Gittenberger" journalOrPublisher="Zoologische Mededelingen" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" pagination="263 - 277" part="48" refId="ref12736" refString="Gittenberger E. 1975. Beitrage zur Kenntnis der Pupillacea. V. Die Spelaeodiscinae, erster Nachtrag. Zoologische Mededelingen 48 (23): 263 - 277." title="Beitrage zur Kenntnis der Pupillacea. V. Die Spelaeodiscinae, erster Nachtrag" type="journal article" year="1975">Gittenberger (1975)</bibRefCitation>
nor anyone else has been able to refind 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gittenberger" authorityYear="1969" box="[520,633,373,399]" class="Gastropoda" family="Spelaeodiscidae" genus="Virpazaria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="ripkeni">
<emphasis box="[520,633,373,399]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">V. ripkeni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
at its alleged type locality or anywhere else in the Virpazar area further discredits the validity of the type locality.
</paragraph>
